        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(codex): honor bound agent exec host policy",
        "body": "## Summary\n- store the binding agent id for newly created Codex app-server conversation bindings\n- pass the stored binding agent id into the Codex native execution guard\n- block bound app-server turns when that stored agent resolves to `tools.exec.host=node`, even without a session key\n\n## Scope\nThis intentionally applies to newly created Codex app-server conversation bindings. Existing saved bindings that predate `data.agentId` can keep the previous fallback behavior until the conversation is detached and rebound.\n\nThat keeps this PR narrow: it does not add migration or legacy binding inference logic.\n\n## Verification\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/codex/src/conversation-binding.test.ts extensions/codex/src/commands.test.ts`\n- `PATH=/Users/jmerhi/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.21.0/installation/bin:$PATH pnpm tsgo:extensions`\n- `PATH=/Users/jmerhi/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.21.0/installation/bin:$PATH pnpm tsgo:test:extensions`\n",
